Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: What is the meaning of this? Where have all the torii gone?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Lots of Nishikese dolls. They're all wearing fox masks.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: It's kind of creepy when I can't see their faces...

Name: Putra
Phrase: Hey Yakky. I think I've just discovered something amazing. Don't be so startled that you fall into a ditch or something again, okay?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: And for the record, I'm not afraid of dolls, okay?

Name: Putra
Phrase: This one's much scarier than dolls with masks on.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Gasp...!?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Putra, don't bully Yakutsk too much. Don't be pretentious, just say it quickly.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Umm, the fact is...

Name: Putra
Phrase: This cave has no way in or out.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Aren't you scared?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Scared.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: V-Very scared.

Name: Putra
Phrase: 'Yes. You said you're scared.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: S-Stop k-kidding with me already, okay?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: It's s-scary to be stuck with d-dolls wearing f-f-fox's masks f-forever!

Name: Putra
Phrase: Oh, it's a rare gem to hear you speaking your mind, Yakky.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Did the masked girl know that this will happen to us? Did she tell us to look for the black torii and then lock us in a cave?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: T-There must be some kind of trick. We have to go through here to get to the top of the mountain. We need to find out what these dolls means...

Name: Putra
Phrase: It looks like the clever, cute little beast ears are already investigating that.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Clever, cute little beast ears?

Name: Putra
Phrase: With Conductor and Queensway. Did they find something weird?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: We can't get back to where we were with sorcery. Maybe there is a way to the summit somewhere in this cave.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Hey, Miyako. There's a big puddle over here. There's something floating in it.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Don't go in there. It might be deeper than it looks.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Yoshino, Miss Miyako, anything on your end?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: It looks like something's floating in a puddle. Maybe it has something to do with Yoshino's curse.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: A boat made of wood with lots of round, rice cracker-like things?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: They're not senbei, they're sandawara. Boats made of woven straw. Straws lids to store rice in straw bags.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Well, a sandawara is also a magic item often used in sorcery.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Then that means Miss Yoshino's curse is... I think it was from this cave!

Name: Miyako
Phrase: No, that's probably not true.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: This is nagashi-bina. They are not tools used for curses.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Nagashi-bina?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: It's one of the rituals in Nishiki. Nina-ningyo are placed on a boat and floated down the river. In some areas, it's still done as an ceremony.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Aren't hina-ningyo the dolls that are displayed during Hinamatsuri?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: There is a theory that the Hinamatsuri began with these nagashi-bina dolls. They are floated down the river with a wish that no illness or misfortune will befall the children. Yoshino is talking about Iris Cloud Nishiki's version of the story.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: It's the same with the Nagashi-bina in Metro. Even our old ceremonies and rituals are the same.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: The shape of the boat varies from region to region. So, the nagashi-bina here must have drifted in from many different places.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: But where did they come from? There are no rivers or waterways in this cave, are there?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: That's what we, the brainiacs are supposed to figure out, Queensway-kun.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Hmm...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: The number of nagashi-bina equals the number of children.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Miyako, by children you mean?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I meant the missing children. The number of children found in the Senbon Torii labyrinth is the same as the number of nagashi-bina dolls here.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I don't think this is a coincidence. Did the dolls that floated down the river called the children? Or did someone else called them...?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Oooh- Miyako is in deduction mode.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I haven't found the answer. But I think I found a connection between the nagashi-bina dolls and the disappearance of the children.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: As expected of Miyako. You're smart. You're clever.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I'm not clever, I just have a lot of information. I did a lot of research here before Yoshino and the others.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Information doesn't just come into your head on its own. You have to know what you need to know in order to solve the problem.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: You see, take Paddington for example. Can memorise everything, but can't reason them out.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Makes sense. That's an easy analogy to understand.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yoshino-chan is the one who is clever. I don't think so hard.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: But you have an idea, don't you, Miss Miyako? Theories or not, I don't mind. Please tell us what you think.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is concerned about how many nagashi-bina we have here, right?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes. And also where these came from. They don't all seem to come from the same place.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: How do you know that?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Look, they come in all shapes and sizes, yes? That's because different regions weave the boats in different ways.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I am an apprentice to a doll master. I can usually tell which nagashi-bina dolls originated from by looking at the shape of the boat. And there are so many nagashi-bina in the same area as the children we sheltered.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Conductor, I have a feeling that this is a major incident. This isn't just an unusual outbreak of being spirited away or Phantom Mist. I don't think this is an incident where the M. Nishiki Railway Army can handle anymore. If left unchecked, there will be more casualties.

Then I should report the situation to Islington and request reinforcements from other Train Knights. To do so, we need to get out of our current predicament and bring back the results of this investigation.
Therefore, I have one request to Miyako as the commander of the SSS.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Sure. Anything.

I want you to captain everyone of Iris Cloud within this Senbon Torii. Miyako belongs to the Special Task Force of the Iris Metro Allied Forces, correct? Then the the Special Task Force is as good as the SSS.
I want all of us to cooperate more actively as companions fighting together. While I have the final say, I still want to respect your opinion, Miyako.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I don't know if an inexperienced person like me is allowed to lead...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Not at all, you're under-selling yourself!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: If it wasn't for you, Miss Miyako, we would still be wandering in the torii labyrinth now. Miss Miyako has a wealth of knowledge both with regards to sorcery and M. Nishiki. It would be much easier for us if Miss Miyako can provide us all sorts of instructions.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is a bit reserved. You should give instructions to Yoshino and friends than to deal with everything yourself.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Besides, Miyako is a little different today. You can be more free like before, can't you?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Are you still anxious without Versailles?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: No, I'm not. I'm fine on my own.
I'm not asking if you're fine on your own. Are you willing to cooperate with us as a member of the SSS? That's what I'm asking.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: ...Yes. That, of course.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: But I might put you all in danger. Because I sometimes can go deep into the darkness without considering any risks...".

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Don't worry. Yoshino and friends are used to that kind of thing.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino wants you to think of it as helping Yoshino and friends. Miyako will do her best for everyone. Everyone will do their best for Miyako. This is important.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: For everyone's sake, to help everyone...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: --I will do whatever it takes to help people.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: ...Oh, sorry. It's nothing. I'm just trying to do my best for everyone.
Thank you, Miyako. I know it might be a burden to you in some way, but whatever we can do to help, just let us know.

If there is anything we should or shouldn't do, let me know immediately. We've been in a lot of danger in Nishiki of Iris Cloud, but we managed it with the help of our sorceress. Miyako, too, you must work with Yoshino to make a breakthrough.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I understand. I don't know if I can do it well, but I will do my best as a member of the unit.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: First of all, we need to find clues to the black torii in order to proceed. I need to talk to everyone, so please ask them all to gather here.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: I'll go get eveyone else!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yeah, that'll be nice.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is back to becoming genki. She is now a child who can work hard together with others.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is smart but a bit, more like, a lot clumsy.
A smart, quiet child. A child who never cries, never rants, never speaks.
Come on, come on, come here. Let's get you dressed.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yoshino-chan? What's wrong?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: No, nothing.
